HEADWORD: Spook
<hw>Spook</hw> <pr>(sp⟦oomac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>spook</ets>; akin to G. <ets>spuk</ets>, Sw. <ets>sp⟦oum⟧ke</ets>,
Dan. <ets>sp⟦oum⟧gelse</ets> a specter, <ets>sp⟦oum⟧ge</ets> to play,
sport, joke, <ets>sp⟦oum⟧g</ets> a play, joke.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
spirit; a ghost; an apparition; a hobgoblin.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>spuke</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Ld. Lytton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The chimaera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

